CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1969, pg. 9 reads: "Executive Ch[i]ef James H. Joyner, Sr., left, of the "Delta Queen" one of the enchanting last paddle wheelers in river service, chats with Capt. Ernest Wagner of New Richmond, Ohio, center, and Stewart Franklin Myles of Memphis, Tenn. Chief Joyner, also a Memphis resident, cam to Pittsburgh last week and fell in love with the city. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Captain Ernest Wagner, Executive Chief James H. Joyner, Sr., and Stewart Franklin Myles, standing on board the Delta Queen
